In this article, President Barack Obama sends a letter to various health care stakeholders, including CEOs, presidents, and chairpersons of different organizations. The President expresses his appreciation for their commitment to health care reform and their pledge to reduce the nation's annual health care spending growth rate by 1.5 percentage points. He emphasizes the importance of controlling health care costs to provide affordable and quality care for all Americans, improve business competitiveness, and reduce budget deficits. The President requests an update from the stakeholders on their progress towards fulfilling this commitment by early June.